<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-21T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="100" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">655.116 Auto/5: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-21T14:00:00-05:00">November 21, 1935—2
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>77. Your 92, November 20, 6 p.m. Culbertson, now in Paris, has been
                                directed to proceed at once to Brussels to consult with you and
                                appropriate Belgian officials concerning the proposed tire quota.
                                Since he was a negotiator of the Belgian trade agreement, the
                                Department would like to have his recommendations before deciding
                                upon its course of action.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>